history.content: I took that course load last semester and it was alright! Although I heard that the Fall iteration of CS189 is generally heavier workload / more difficult than the Spring iteration. I felt like CS170 homeworks were more creative, which may take more / less time depending on the person, and CS189 homework were more directly related to lecture / course notes. The CS170 final was mostly multiple choice / short answer online, which was kind of weird to me. CS189's exams were about the same as in-person. Overall it felt like it was slightly more chill than taking three techs, but homework are a decent amount of work.
